-- MOVES-Nitesh Mistry joins Deutsche Asset from Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi
-- 
-- Wed Aug 13, 2014 06:27AM EDT
-- None



Aug 13 (Reuters) - Deutsche Asset & Wealth Management, a unit of German lender Deutsche Bank AG <DBKGn.DE>, said it appointed Nitesh Mistry as director to oversee its infrastructure debt investment business in Europe.

Mistry was previously a director in the European investment banking division of Japan's Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi UFJ [MTFGTU.UL]. Mistry, who has more than 15 years of experience in the infrastructure market, will be based in London.